args: Vice Captain of the White Sparrows\nPatia
This day is the reward for all the months\nI spent toiling away at my duties.
I have a brand-new set of swimwear,\nand a perfect beach lying in front of me.
Here I go! It's a full-tilt sprint straight\ninto the beautiful blue ocean!
Eeeek! Save me, my apple dumpling!\nThere are nasty fiends strewn across\nthis entire beach!
This is truly a sad day for beachgoing,\nmy berry buckle. Let's go back to town\nat once and find a less risky vacation.
Berry Buckle is right—this beach is\ncrammed to the gills with fiends!
I know not what is causing this, but as a\nknight, I cannot stand by and do nothing.\nTime to deal with this problem.
Seems they're not much threat one-on-one.\nI'll take them all out and restore peace\nto the beach!
And then, it's back to vacation!\nLet's do this!
Will this never end?! What in the name of\nsnow cones is going ON with this beach?!
If this keeps up, I'll spend my entire\nvacation slaying fiends!
No! I refuse to allow such a tragedy!
I WILL solve this! For the sake of peace on\nthe beach, and my vacation!
I need to figure out where all these\nfiends are coming from and cut the\nproblem off at the heart.
Blast, this is no mere letter...\nSomeone has challenged me!

Gar, Ye Fool Knight,

How DARE ye lay a finger on me underlings!
As their cap'n, I'm challengin' ya to a true
duel of the seas, so I am!

The form'a yer humiliation will be a beach
volleyball match fair and true. Now see that
yer yellow-bellied self is on the beach tomorrow!

—Sincerely, Barbary
Who is this Barbary person, and why is\nshe challenging me to beach volleyball?
Also, why did she write the letter with\nan accent? That's just unnecessary.
Permit US to answer your query!
Barbary is the name of a fiend who\nwas once a pirate in this area.
After everyone helped put her in her place\nand I gave her a stern talking-to, she\nswore to give up piracy and violence.
As she is deathly afraid of having to sit\nthrough another of my lectures, she's been\nkeeping to her word thus far.

But it looks like she found a loophole:
If she challenges foes to beach volleyball,
she can use nonviolent means to take
down her enemies with impunity.

Do not take her challenge lightly!
Barbary has six arms and legs,
so her ball-handling capabilities
are on a whole other level.
She used this strategy to eliminate her\ncompetition and take over the beach.
After she took down the reigning\nvolleyball champ, all the other\nlocals refused to go near her.

They've been searching the land trying to
find players who can hold their own
against her, but all to no avail—until
the three of us showed up, that is.
...Why do we actually have to play her,\nthough?
When one has been challenged by the ball,\none must WIN by the ball!

As we already sent Barbary packing once,
the locals thought we could do it again.
In fact, we were in the process of
searching for one final teammate.
What do you say, Patia?\nWill you join our cause?
And you're SURE this has to be volleyball.\nWe can't just...you know? Crush our\nenemies and drive them before us?
Such a strategy ill befits a knight!
Well, I suppose it WOULD be bad form\nto stick a lance in someone during a\nvolleyball match...
I'm starting to feel you have a point.\nWe must win by the ball.
As a White Sparrow, I shall not be outdone\nby my enemies—whether by sword, lance,\nspike-covered doom axe, or volleyball!
We will defeat them and return peace to\nthe beach—and THEN I will finally be\nable to take my damned vacation!
The next morning, at the net...
Gahar har har! And here I thought I'd be\nfacin' a wily foe, seein' as how ye sent\nall me underlings packin' in tears...
But yer just a buncha beach bums what\ncan't hold a candle to ol' Barbary!\nGahaaaar har har har yar!
How can I ever face Elisanne again with\nsuch an ignominious defeat hanging over\nme like a pall?
We need a new strategy. Best to withdraw\nfor now and live to serve another day.
Yar, ye blasted cod-livers can face me as\nmany times as ye like—it won't do ye a\nbit'a good, so it won't!
Now, if ye've learned yer lesson,\nget off me beach.

There ain't man nor beast what can lay
me to ground in beach volleyball,
which means this beach is pirate land!
Gahaaaar har har! Yar har ho!
Fine. We withdraw for now.\nBut this is NOT over.
We'll win next time, Barbary!\nYou WILL get what's owed you!
